specJson.label: One Hot Encoder Model
specJson.description:
In machine learning, one-hot is a group of bits among which the legal combinations of values are only those with a single high (1) bit and all the others low (0). A similar implementation in which all bits are '1' except one '0' is sometimes called one-cold. In statistics, dummy variables represent a similar technique for representing categorical data.

This function transforms the features using the result of One Hot Encoder.

out_table.desc: Output table. It contains the input table columns and one-hot encoded columns.

specJson.summary: This function encodes categorical integer features using a one-hot, also known as one-of-K, scheme.

md: # One Hot Encoder Model This function encodes categorical integer features using a one-hot, also known as one-of-K, scheme. ## Description In machine learning, one-hot is a group of bits among which the legal combinations of values are only those with a single high (1) bit and all the others low (0). A similar implementation in which all bits are '1' except one '0' is sometimes called one-cold. In statistics, dummy variables represent a similar technique for representing categorical data. This function transforms the features using the result of One Hot Encoder. Reference - ## Properties ### VA #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Data in a Table. 2. **model***: (Model) Trained One Hot Encoder Model #### OUTPUT 1. **out_table**: (Table) Output table. It contains the input table columns and one-hot encoded columns. #### PARAMETER This function has no parameter. ### Python #### USAGE ``` one_hot_encoder_model(table, model) ``` #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Data in a Table. 2. **model***: (Model) Trained One Hot Encoder Model #### OUTPUT 1. **out_table**: (Table) Output table. It contains the input table columns and one-hot encoded columns. #### PARAMETER ## Example ### VA **[Related Tutorial]** **[Sample Model]** In this tutorial workflow, sample_iris data is used as input of One Hot Encoder function. And the One Hot Encoder output model and sample_iris Table are used as input of One Hot Encoder Model function. The ouput of this function is a Table that contains the input table columns and one-hot encoded columns. ### Python ``` from brightics.function.extraction import one_hot_encoder_model input_table = inputs[0] input_model = models[0] res = one_hot_encoder_model(table = input_table, model = input_model) output = res['out_table'] ``` In this python script, a trained One Hot Encoder model is applied to the input data to convert given columns into one hot vectors.
